pikes had placed a bid of an undisclosed amount to the trustee handling the=
 bankruptcy of Helios and Matheson Analytics (HMNY), the former parent comp=
any of MoviePass.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"I can confirm that we ac=
quired MoviePass out of bankruptcy on Wednesday," Spikes said in a statemen=
t to Insider. "We are thrilled to have it back and are exploring the possib=
ility of relaunching soon. Our pursuit to reclaim the brand was encouraged =
by the continued interest from the moviegoing community. We believe, if don=
e properly, theatrical subscription can play an instrumental role in liftin=
g moviegoing attendance to new heights." ...</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">Spikes hopes to relaunch MoviePass sometime next year.=C2=A0A new site ha=
s been created for the relaunch, iwantmoviepass.com, and its logo will now =
feature a black background with white lettering, ditching its previous red =
background. Here is the new logo:</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">The new logo is somehow not a picture of Doge. He=E2=80=99d better be s=
elling non-fungible tokens of movie tickets. He=E2=80=99d better be teaming=
 up with AMC to get people free MoviePass shares with <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25710228.278663/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
