cturer on sustainability at the Yale School of Management and the co-direct=
or of the school=E2=80=99s environment and business center.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">This interest reflects an increase in jobs that require kn=
owledge in environmental, social and governance, or E.S.G., topics.</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Global sustainable investment topped $30 trillion =
in 2019 =E2=80=94 up 68 percent since 2014, according to McKinsey. That has=
 created more jobs in the field, which has pushed salaries higher for worke=
rs with the necessary skills. In addition, companies say they=E2=80=99re ha=
ving an easier time recruiting junior employees than senior leaders in E.S.=
G. roles, which could give younger workers an advantage in climbing the cor=
porate ladder (or allow them to start at a higher rung) than for the typica=
l jobs for M.B.A. graduates.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Y=
